		{"id":"4e469a37744930b0","type":"text","text":"as far as behavior goes, it would probably be the wisest to use state machines. they are the most versatile and fit with the composition philosophy i'm going for.\n\nstates would be their own godot 4 `Node` and depending on their function would only need access to certain components (or better yet, signals emitted by these components).\n\nfor example, if a state allowed for switching to a different state based on if the parent creature was harmed or not, the creature's `HealthComponent` would emit a signal if its health was lowered by cause of an attack. the state would hook onto that signal and if the signal was emitted, then the state would switch.\n\nstates should not hardcode their adjacent states; transitions should be exported in the godot inspector.\n\na `StateMachine` parent node would have all the `State` nodes as children.\n\n```gdscript\n# state example\n# note that the base class for State would probably have a state_machine variable in it\n\nvar state_machine: StateMachine\n@export var state_1: State\n@export var flee_state: State\n@export var health_component: HealthComponent\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tstate_machine = get_parent()\n\tif state_machine is not StateMachine:\n\t\tpush_error(\"Parent is not StateMachine!\")\n\t\t\n\tif health_component:\n\t\thealth_component.health_lost.connect(_on_health_lost)\n\nfunc enter() -> void:\n\t# stuff here\n\nfunc update(delta: float) -> void:\n\t# logic here\n\t\n\tif condition:\n\t\tstate_machine.transition(state_1)\n\nfunc physics_update(delta: float) -> void:\n\t# logic here which involves movement\n\t# this might not be necessary based on how i set things up\n\nfunc exit() -> void:\n\t# stuff here\n\nfunc _on_health_lost(amount: float, source: Node) -> void:\n\tif source.is_in_group(\"creature\"):\n\t\tstate_machine.transition(rage_state)\n\n```\n\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name StateMachine\n\nsignal state_switched(old_state: State, new_state: State)\n\nvar current_state: State\n\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.update(delta)\n\t\nfunc _physics_process(delta: float) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.physics_update(delta)\n\nfunc switch(new_state: State) -> void:\n\tcurrent_state.exit()\n\tstate_switched.emit(current_state, new_state)\n\tcurrent_state = new_state\n\tcurrent_state.enter()\n```","x":-21350,"y":-21712,"width":580,"height":1600},
		{"id":"d4ecb49fd8a5c8da","type":"text","text":"```gdscript\nextends Node\nclass_name TargetSeeker\n\nsignal target_found(target: Node2D)\nsignal target_lost()\n\n@export var detection_radius: float = 128.0\n@export var target_groups: Array[String] = [\"food\"]\n@export var vision_angle: float = 360.0\n@export var wall_collision_layer: int = 0\n\nvar current_target: Node2D = null\nvar last_known_position: Vector2\n\nfunc find_nearest_target(from_position: Vector2, facing_direction: Vector2) -> Node2D:\n\tvar best_target: Node2D = null\n\tvar best_distance: float = INF\n\t\n\tfor group_name in target_groups:\n\t\tvar potential_targets = owner.get_tree().get_nodes_in_group(group_name)\n\t\t\n\t\tfor target in potential_targets:\n\t\t\t# entity does not exist?\n\t\t\tif not is_instance_valid(target):\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\tvar to_target = target.global_position - from_position\n\t\t\tvar distance = to_target.length()\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# too far away?\n\t\t\tif distance > detection_radius:\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# outside vision cone?\n\t\t\tif vision_angle < 360.0:\n\t\t\t\tvar angle_to_target = facing_direction.angle_to(to_target)\n\t\t\t\tif abs(angle_to_target) > deg_to_rad(vision_angle) / 2.0):\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t# line of sight check; can we actually see it?\n\t\t\tif not has_line_of_sight(from_position, target.global_position):\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\tif distance < best_ddstance:\n\t\t\t\tbest_target = target\n\t\t\t\tbest_distance = distance\n\t\t\n\tif best_target != current_target:\n\t\tif current_target != null:\n\t\t\ttarget_lost.emit()\n\t\tif best_target != null:\n\t\t\ttarget_found.emit(best_target)\n\t\tcurrent_target = best_target\n\t\t\n\tif best_target:\n\t\tlast_known_position = best_target.global_position\n\t\t\n\treturn best_target\n\t\nfunc has_line_of_sight(from: Vector2, to: Vector2) -> bool:\n\tvar space_state = owner.get_world_2d().direct_space_state\n\t\n\tvar query = PhysicsRaycast2DQuery.create(from, to)\n\tquery.collision_mask = wall_collision_layer\n\tquery.collide_with_areas: false\n\tquery.collide_with_bodies = true\n\tquery.exclude = [owner]\n\t\n\tvar result = space_state.intersect_ray(query)\n\t\n\tif not result:\n\t\treturn true\n\t\t\n\tvar hit_distance = from.distance_to(result.position)\n\tvar target_distance = from.distance_to(to)\n\t\n\treturn hit_distance >= target_distance\n\t\nfunc get_direction_to_target(from_position: Vector2) -> Vector2:\n\tif curernt_target and is_instance_valid(current_target):\n\t\treturn (current_target.global_position - from_position).normalized()\n\telif last_known_position:\n\t\t# move toward last known position if we lost sight\n\t\treturn (last_known_position - from_position).normalized()\n\treturn Vector2.ZERO \n```","x":-19990,"y":-21712,"width":700,"height":1600},
		{"id":"52e8c52b0943cda1","type":"text","text":"graze\n\nactions:\n\n1. pathfind near a plant\n2. begin eating\n\t1. lower the plant's nutrition\n\t2. raise the animal's nutrition\n\t3. lower the animal's hunger","x":-17380,"y":-20648,"width":681,"height":318},
		{"id":"64a97b71170ce443","type":"text","text":"attack_nearby\n\npriority evaluation:\n1. search for nearby creatures (eyecomponent)\n2. set target as nearest creature\n3. if a creature is within a specified distance, priority goes up\n\nintent generation:\n1. \"attack\" as action\n2. and post the target (stored as variable in goal)\n\nactions:\n1. look at target\n2. every interval, swipe\n\t1. activate hurtbox for a frame","x":-17380,"y":-21021,"width":521,"height":373},
		{
			"id":"9240d98c9c4c3b00",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Brain\n\nBrain (Node)\n1. has `Goal` nodes as children\n2. places `Goal` nodes in an array\n3. loops through all `Goal` nodes using `evaluate_priority()`\n4. sorts array based on priority values\n5. generates intent from highest priority goal every frame\n6. calls `execute_intent()` from `IntentExecutor`\n\nComponents map **action strings** to functions, which will then be called every frame by `execute_intent()` from the `IntentExecutor`\n\n```gdscript\nclass_name Brain\nextends Node\n\nsignal intent_changed(old_intent: Intent, new_intent: Intent)\nsignal goal_changed(old_goal_name: String, new_goal_name: String, new_priority: float)\n\n@export var creature: Node2D\n\n@export var personality: Dictionary[String, float] = {\n\t\"aggression\": 0.0,\n\t\"bravery\": 0.0,\n\t\"dominance\": 0.0,\n\t\"energy\": 0.0,\n\t\"nervous\": 0.0,\n\t\"sympathy\": 0.0\n}\n```\n\n```gdscript\n# goal management\nvar goals: Array[Goal] = []\nvar current_intent: Intent = null\nvar current_goal: Goal = null\n\n# memory system for persistent state\nvar memory: Dictionary = {}\n\n@export var priority_threshold: float = 1.2 # new goal must be this much higher to switch\n@export var min_goal_durations: float = 0.1 # minimum time before switching goals\n\nvar time_since_goal_change: float = 0.0\n\nfunc _ready() -> void:\n\tdetermine_personality()\n\t_gather_goals()\n\t\n\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\nfunc _process(delta: float) -> void:\n\ttime_since_goal_change += delta\n\t\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\t\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _gather_goals() -> void:\n\tgoals.clear()\n\tfor child in get_children():\n\t\tif child is Goal:\n\t\t\tgoals.append(child)\n\t\t\t\n\tif goals.is_empty():\n\t\tpush_warning(\"[Brain] No goals found for creature: %s\" % creature.name)\n\t\t\n\nfunc _evaluate_goals() -> Goal:\n\tvar best_goal: Goal = null\n\tvar highest_priority: float = -INF\n\t\n\tfor goal in goals:\n\t\tvar evaluated_priority = goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\t\tif evaluated_priority > highest_priority:\n\t\t\thighest_priority = evaluated_priority\n\t\t\tbest_goal = goal\n\t\t\t\n\treturn best_goal\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc _should_switch_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> bool:\n\tif current_goal == null:\n\t\treturn new_goal != null\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif new_goal == current_goal:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tif time_since_goal_change < min_goal_duration:\n\t\treturn false\n\t\t\n\tvar current_priority = current_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\tvar new_priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\n\t# only switch if new goal is significantly better\n\treturn new_priority > current_priority + priority_threshold\n\t\n\t\nfunc _switch_to_goal(new_goal: Goal) -> void:\n\tvar old_intent = current_intent\n\tvar old_goal_name = current_goal.name if current_goal else \"none\"\n\t\n\tcurrent_goal = new_goal\n\ttime_since_goal_change = 0.0\n\t\n\tif new_goal == null:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = Intent.new()\n\t\tcurrent_intent.action = \"idle\"\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = \"idle\"\n\telse:\n\t\tcurrent_intent = new_goal.generate_intent(self)\n\t\tcurrent_intent.goal_name = new_goal.name\n\t\tcurrent_intent.priority = new_goal.evaluate_priority(self)\n\t\t\n\tgoal_changed.emit(old_goal_name, current_intent.goal_name, current_intent.priority)\n\tintent_changed.emit(old_intent, current_intent)\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc get_current_intent() -> Intent:\n\treturn current_intent\n\t\nfunc force_reevaluate() -> void:\n\tvar best_goal = _evaluate_goals()\n\tvar old_threshold = priority_threshold\n\tpriority_threshold = -INF\n\tif _should_switch_goal(best_goal):\n\t\t_switch_to_goal(best_goal)\n\tpriority_threshold = old_threshold\n\t\nfunc determine_personality() -> void:\n\tpersonality[\"aggression\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"bravery\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"dominance\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"energy\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"nervous\"] = randf()\n\tpersonality[\"sympathy\"] = randf()\n```\n\n```gdscript\nfunc remember(key: String, value: Variant) -> void:\n\tmemory[key] = value\n\t\nfunc recall(key: String, default = null) -> Variant:\n\treturn memory.get(key, default)\n\t\nfunc forget(key: String) -> void:\n\tmemory.erase(key)\n\t\nfunc has_memory(key: String) -> bool:\n\treturn memory.has(key)\n\t\nfunc clear_memory() -> void:\n\tmemory.clear()\n\t\nfunc get_memory_keys() -> Array:\n\treturn memory.keys()\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{
				"shape":null,
				"border":null
			},
			"x":-18170,
			"y":-23651,
			"width":540,
			"height":2960
