			"width":540,
			"height":320
		},
		{
			"id":"4fae59d27d015e56",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Let's make a universal controller for navigating between and selecting UI elements.\n\nThis element will be a `Node2D` \"hand\" and will interact with special `Control` nodes.\n\n```gdscript\nextends Control\nclass_name InteractableUI\n\nfunc on_select() -> void:\n\tpass\n\t\nfunc on_interact() -> void:\n\tpass\n```\n\nThings that can happen in a gui:\n- navigation (element selection)\n- activation (element is clicked)\n- context change\n- menu change\nThe hand needs to support \"picking up\" and \"placing down\" elements, which means \n\n```gdscript\nextends Node2D\n\nvar interactable_group: Array[InteractableUI]\n@export var animator: SpriteAnimator\n\n\n\nfunc switch_interactable_group(group: Array[InteractableUI], currently_selected: int) -> void:\n\tpass\n\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-17270,
			"y":-8896,
			"width":840,
			"height":700
		},
		{
			"id":"50c47ca532d574c9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# design 4\n\n| design 4                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |\n| --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| every creature has a value which is simultaneously hunger, energy, and \"mana\" <br><br>i.e. a resource which drains over time, is replenished through consuming food or other items, and can be drained through casting special abilities.<br><br>when this resource is drained completely, the creature begins to take damage over time |\n| this resource can be called 'aether' or 'ichor'                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         |\n| this acts as a drive for creatures to seek food and replenish themselves, making creature behavior more interesting                                                                                                                                                                                                                     |\n| this also acts as a drive for the player to not only survive but also strategically use abilities only when necessary                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-13447,
			"y":-5281,
			"width":460,
			"height":440
		},
		{
			"id":"f4249f30fb0d6c9f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# todo 6/14/2026\n",
