		{
			"id":"bec54d213673b22c",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"---\n\n---\nhow do i even do this?\n\nthere are numerous systems that need to know about the anthurium, and the fact that i want the anthurium to be dynamic is causing trouble\n\n`GameState` needs a reference to all anthurium cores\n\nwhen spawning a core, emit a signal that the GameState recognizes so that it can update its array\n\nalso every part needs to keep track of how many parts there are.\n\nehhh i think i have to have a global anthurium node which keeps track of things. that would be easiest.\n\nim struggling\ni have a growth node which needs access to the anthurium brain node. i think that the resolve part function should live here because it will store the active parts and their references.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12027,
			"y":-7786,
			"width":580,
			"height":660
		},
		{
			"id":"4f4f05332ad03afc",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"**liminal/threshold**\nnuminous\nliminality\napophenia: seeing meaningful patterns in randomness\nkenosis\numbra\n**longing/melancholy**\nhiraeth\nsehnsucht\nsaudade\nlacuna: an absent gap; something missing\nvellichor\n**awe/dread**\napricity\nineffability\ntremendum: overwhelming, terror-tinged awe\nabysm\ngloaming\n**hidden/inner**\nanamnesis: a deep unforgetting; recollection of something beyond memory\nocculence\nquietude\nnescience\ninteriority\n**dissolution/transcendence**\napeiron: the boundless, formless infinite\npleroma\nataraxia\nmetempsychosis\nekstasis\n**tension/unease**\ndysphoria\nparesthesia\nennui\nacedia: a hollow spiritual numbness; listlessness of the soul\ntorpor",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12690,
			"y":-8186,
			"width":620,
			"height":740
		},
		{
			"id":"39cf97c64bf5cc9f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# The Anthurium\n\nThe Anthurium is an ancient godlike plant entity which bends and blooms reality into new shapes and life.\n\nThe Anthurium has no malice or agenda; it simply weaves in and out of reality, giving the arena its heartbeat and the origin of life inside it.\n\nCreatures are bloomed from the Anthurium.\n\nWhen the Anthurium spreads enough or absorbs enough matter, it triggers a **bloom event**, causing new creatures to erupt from the growth. The creatures it spawns are determined by the kind of matter it had consumed before the bloom event.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-18690,
			"y":-6849,
			"width":400,
			"height":490
		},
		{
			"id":"21f5e659c7e03df9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Final results screen",
			"styleAttributes":{},
