		{
			"id":"d3ee0f3aeba66c26",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# oops performance issue\nthis is bad news. so the hide in invisible tiles component is gonna cause a lot of lag if there are a lot of entities hooked onto that signal.\n\ni'm probably gonna have to invent some sort of system to only broadcast signals within chunks.\n\nso if a cell is changed in chunk (1, 1) then that signal is only broadcast to entities in nearby chunks.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11294,
			"y":-8086,
			"width":440,
			"height":400
		},
		{
			"id":"86a51ec5217604c6",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"2026-04-08\n\nfor now, it's probably wise to keep the anthurium's mechanics random and add in some smarts later. it's better to just get something out there right now.\n\nlet's try and make a core that spawns a growth node every 5 seconds.\n\na growth node behaves like this:\n1. initialize timer to switch to creating a plant part\n2. loop this\n\t1. take a step\n\t2. spawn flower\n\t3. wait\n3. after time elapses, spawn a plant part\n4. kill self",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12027,
			"y":-8186,
			"width":580,
			"height":380
		},
		{"id":"947dd3c9fa7f95bf","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif_hub-1675329364.gif","x":-13638,"y":-17703,"width":484,"height":272},
		{"id":"a4e6fbb4590defe7","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif-trinketwisp-1643782697440_7u88-2920988492.gif","x":-13638,"y":-18245,"width":484,"height":272},
		{"id":"17c89ec46c1d8b35","type":"file","file":"assets/mina/gif-bossstinky-1643782697452_mcu8.1080-723182484.gif","x":-13638,"y":-17973,"width":484,"height":272},
		{"id":"586ed1603f1abc63","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/comit.gif","x":-14540,"y":-18165,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"104e2084661e3a7b","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/tad17_12.gif","x":-14940,"y":-17765,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"71111d22c2b5a521","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/runner_0.gif","x":-14540,"y":-17765,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"675bebe810b95b59","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/picotachi_74_2025.gif","x":-14940,"y":-18165,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"901a911549e5ecf5","type":"file","file":"assets/pico/pippitron_4.gif","x":-14940,"y":-18390,"width":400,"height":225},
		{
			"id":"71e315751debe66d",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"I would like to rework the ability manager to support context sensitive abilities.\n\nHow would this work?\n\nIf you are playing as Pip, then SPACE is the swipe ability, but if he gets near an interactable object, then the ability manager should recognize that and switch abilities only within that context.\n\nAnother example: An entity has the \"hand\" ability, which allows them to pick up another entity. Once the entity has been picked up, the context changes and the \"pick up\" ability should change into a \"toss\" ability.\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-14012,
			"y":-4221,
			"width":671,
			"height":380
		},
		{
			"id":"3f9f9b2dc21d0bb9",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"1. What is the core lesson your game teaches?\n2. How does your game keep itself interesting?\n3. At what point will your game become boring?",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-19370,
			"y":-4026,
			"width":600,
			"height":220
		},
		{
			"id":"0e72df565957a435",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"define cell patterns (4x4, 8x8, 16x16) and allow them to repeat NSEW (recursive function based on a percentage chance)",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-19390,
			"y":-4246,
			"width":440,
			"height":190
		},
		{
			"id":"908b77363a343725",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Designing more fun\nThe game takes place on a single 64x64 board, so there must be a dramatic arc; ecosystems must change drastically as time goes on.\n\nThe Anthurium, the creatures, and terrain should all have relationships with one another that the player can exploit.\n\n> When designing a creature, think: how does this create an interesting decision for the player?\n\nPip can pick up creatures less massive than itself, granting the possibility to *squeeze* a creature to use its ability. These abilities should always feel **situationally powerful** rather than **generically good**.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-20050,
			"y":-4246,
			"width":640,
			"height":480
		},
		{
			"id":"e9b91ac80e873453",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Anthurium\nSix emotional parameters (*Esoterica*) track the Anthurium's state.\nThey are:\n- *Felicity* (joyful contentment)\n- *Furor* (divine rage)\n- *Lacuna* (hollow emptiness)\n- *Tremendum* (awe-inspiring power)\n- *Acedia* (torpor and apathy)\n- *Anamnesis* (awakening and recalling)\n\nWhen it blooms, those six values form a vector that selects the nearest matching `BloomEvent` by cosine similarity. The vector's angle picks the event; its magnitude sets how intense it is.\n\nThere are three bloom tiers.\n- Flowering (quiet, ambient)\n- Bloom (notable, significant dunegon-altering event)\n- Final Bloom (boss event, ends the round)\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11585,
			"y":-3876,
			"width":520,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"ed03857320848252",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Heartbeat\nThe Anthurium pulses on a semi-regular interval, sending a small amount of bloom potential through its root network. Potential flows outward and accumulates at end nodes (the outermost roots). When an end node's accumulated potential crosses a threshold, it blooms.\n\nThis means:\n- a larger network = more end nodes = potential is spread thinner, blooms are slower per end node that exists! (the anthurium will need to create more hearts to beat stronger)\n- a severed or small network = potential concentrates = blooms fire faster and harder\n- the player can influence bloom timing by suppressing or letting the Anthurium grow",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11025,
			"y":-3876,
			"width":520,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"c719c3155a842307",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Ichor\nIchor is the lifeblood of the dungeon and acts as the liquid energy that creatures use to stay alive and flourish.\n\nThe Anthurium is the dungeon's primary Ichor source. It slowly generates Ichor, which it uses to beat its heart. It produces fruit which have a high concentration of Ichor. A larger Anthurium network means more Ichor generated, meaning more Ichor flowing into the ecosystem.\n\nThe Anthurium can also be predatory and eat creatures or terrain when it's either low on Ichor or cannot produce enough on its own.\n\nIchor transfer happens through\n- creatures dying and dropping meat/food on the ground\n- predators eating prey directly\n- symbiotic creatures absorbing ichor directly from anthurium\n\nDiminishment:\n- passive time decay on every creature\n- ability usage\n- bloom events consuming ichor from the network to fire\n- ichor lost to entropy on creature death\n\nMultiplication:\n- closed predator/prey loops\n- high felicity accelerates root generation\n- creature reproduction introduces new ichor containers into the ecosystem\n- dense food sources act as injections",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-10465,
			"y":-3876,
			"width":1080,
			"height":560
		},
		{
			"id":"2a961f937a38293f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Anthurium's Esoterica\nThe Anthurium keeps track of six parameters as it lives on in the dungeon.\n\n*Felicity*\n> Things are as they should be. \n\nFelicity rises when \n- the network spreads unopposed\n- when creatures are born from blooms and survive\n- when ichor is plentiful\n\nFelicity falls slowly when \n- any of those are not true\n\n*Furor*\n> Divine anger triggered by violation. \n> High furor blooms should feel retaliatory.\n\nFuror rises sharply when \n- Anthurium parts are damaged or destroyed\n- when a creature born from it is killed\n- when terrain near the network is destroyed\n\nFuror decays slowly.\n\n*Lacuna*\n> The ache of absence. \n\nLacuna rises when \n- rooms are empty of creatures\n- creatures are killed\n- when the network has been severed or fragmented\n- when a long time passes without a bloom\n- when items are used or consumed\n\nLacune falls when\n- entities are created/summoned\n\n*Tremendum*\n> Awe triggered by scale or power. \n\nTremendum rises sharply when \n- large amounts of damage occur in a short window\n- when a powerful creature dies nearby\n- when the network reaches a new size threshold\n- when a new terrain type is reached by the Anthurium\n\nTremendum decays slowly.\n\n*Acedia*\n> Hollow spiritual numbness, the soul gone still\n> The plant is festering.\n\nAcedia rises when\n- being ignored\n- it doesn't have enough room to grow\n- being starved\n\nAcedia falls when\n- the plant spreads\n- entities interact with the plant\n\n*Anamnesis*\n> Slow, inexorable.\n> The plant is waking up.\n\nAnamnesis rises when\n- time elapses\n- the Anthurium absorbs ichor over the run\n\nAnamnesis falls when\n- the plant's parts are destroyed\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-9345,
			"y":-3876,
			"width":610,
			"height":1621
		},
		{
			"id":"9abda5b51f83bfe8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"```gdscript\nenum BehaviorClass{\n\t## does not attack other creatures or flees when nearby other creatures\n\tPASSIVE, \n\t## only retaliates if provoked\n\tREACTIVE, \n\t## actively hunts other creatures\n\tPREDATORY, \n\t## violent towards other creatures\n\tFERAL, \n\t## does not care about other creatures\n\tALOOF\n\t}\n\n\n\nenum ConsumerType{\n\t## hunger is lessened passively over time given a condition\n\tAMBIENT, \n\t## hunger is lessened when nearby a specific entity\n\tPROXIMITY, \n\t## hunger is lessened by consuming entities\n\tCONSUMER, \n\t## hunger is lessened through unconventional means\n\tESOTERIC, \n\t## does not have hunger\n\tEXEMPT\n\t}\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-14076,
			"y":-3381,
			"width":669,
			"height":640
		},
		{
			"id":"89b445b40d230576",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Creatures\nEach creature is separated into categories which describe its basic behaviors and tendencies. More primitive creatures have a drive to live, survive, and reproduce. Other creatures have other goals that they pursue.\n\n| Behavior Class | Description                                                           |\n| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| PASSIVE        | Does not attack other creatures OR flees when nearby other creatures. |\n| REACTIVE       | Only retaliates if provoked.                                          |\n| PREDATORY      | Actively hunts other creatures to satiate itself.                     |\n| FERAL          | Violent towards other creatures.                                      |\n| ALOOF          | Does not care about other creatures.                                  |\n\n| Consumer Type | Description                                                 |\n| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |\n| AMBIENT       | Ichor is replenished passively over time given a condition. |\n| PROXIMITY     | Ichor is replenished when nearby a specific entity.         |\n| CONSUMER      | Ichor is replenished by consuming entities                  |\n| ESOTERIC      | Ichor is replenished through unconventional means.          |\n| EXEMPT        | Does not have ichor.                                        |\nCreatures will have emergent relationships with each other through their needs and behaviors (without explicitly scripted events). Creature relationships are not hardcoded, instead creatures will react to others based on their actions and intent.\nCreatures can interact with, damage, heal, use abilities on, move with, and generally affect other entities, including the Anthurium.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11585,
			"y":-3376,
			"width":1080,
			"height":680
		},
		{
			"id":"05d1f12ea7c2f641",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"**creature pack BETA**\n\nSLASHER HOUSE (FERAL CONSUMER)\nFast predator, but can only see and target moving entities.\n**Slash**: A wide melee attack.\n\nSHADE (FERAL ESOTERIC)\nHides in walls and jumps out at targets. Replenishes ichor by being in walls.\n\nSPINER (PREDATORY CONSUMER)\nCovered in spines. Does contact damage. Spines are poisonous.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-19490,
			"y":-3136,
			"width":540,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"07a9f7ad62774d27",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"**creature pack ALPHA**\n\nBLOATER (PASSIVE CONSUMER)\nSlow, fat, and delicious. Eats dropped items and terrain debris.\n**Gut Spew**: Vomits up everything in its inventory in a spray. If there's nothing in the inventory, spit instead.\n**Swallow**: Swallows whatever item is in front of the entity.\n\nSHROOM (PASSIVE AMBIENT)\nStationary. Releases a spore cloud when disturbed. Cloud type varies.\n**Spore**: Emits a spore cloud. The effects of which are dependent on the entity's aggression and energy.\n\nMIROOK (PASSIVE CONSUMER)\nSlow creature with a reflective carapace. Projectiles and entities bounce off it. \n(how tf am i gonna do this)",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-20070,
			"y":-3136,
			"width":540,
			"height":460
		},
		{
			"id":"03bc771e89492ec8",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Game Loop\nThree arbitrary phases will occur during a round!\n\n**Dormancy**\n- Anthurium is slow and its Esoterica has not had much time to flourish, so mostly Flowerings occur.\n- The player is able to peacefully explore the starting dungeon layout and discover what creatures inhabit the map.\n\n**Blooming**\n- Blooms start, changing the conditions and makeup of the game board.\n- The ecosystem has matured slightly and developed.\n\n**Imminence**\n- The Anthurium has spread throughout the board and blooms are more potent.\n- The Final Bloom is approaching, so the player must prepare.\n\n\nThe Final Bloom will occur when the Anthurium's *Esoterica* magnitude reaches over a certain threshold (50? 100? threshold increases per round completed? TBD)\n\nBe careful! If the dungeon is damaged too much, there's a chance that there will be an Ichor famine. It's very hard to come back from this, and the Anthurium is likely to die, causing all the inhabitants of the dungeon to starve.\n\nWhen a round ends, \n- the Anthurium's esoterica will be reset to 0 \n- the anthurium's esoterica will rise faster\n- the threshold for the anthurium's final bloom will be higher, so more intense/potent blooms are more likely to happen as the run continues and the player completes rounds.\n- the map will be regenerated from a different seed\n- the anthurium will be placed in a random location on the map\n- the anthurium's size will be reset down to its initial size\n- creature spawns will be reset and randomized\n- some rare creatures encountered in the last round are more likely to be encountered in following rounds\n\nTechnically, the game can go on infinitely if the player is skilled enough.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-10465,
			"y":-3276,
			"width":520,
			"height":960
		},
		{"id":"519c6e0a0dcde7a2","type":"file","file":"assets/Pasted image 20260607234721.png","x":-19330,"y":-3696,"width":959,"height":480},
		{
			"id":"2d264c628b7f5fae",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"\n| Behavior Class | Description                                                           |\n| -------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| PASSIVE        | Does not attack other creatures OR flees when nearby other creatures. |\n| REACTIVE       | Only retaliates if provoked.                                          |\n| PREDATORY      | Actively hunts other creatures to satiate itself.                     |\n| FERAL          | Violent towards other creatures.                                      |\n| ALOOF          | Does not care about other creatures.                                  |\n\n| Consumer Type | Description                                                 |\n| ------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |\n| AMBIENT       | Ichor is replenished passively over time given a condition. |\n| PROXIMITY     | Ichor is replenished when nearby a specific entity.         |\n| CONSUMER      | Ichor is replenished by consuming entities                  |\n| ESOTERIC      | Ichor is replenished through unconventional means.          |\n| EXEMPT        | Does not have ichor.                                        |\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-20050,
			"y":-3596,
			"width":640,
			"height":420
		},
		{
			"id":"8e64f4739a27f4f7",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"There's two ways this could be handled.\n\n1. The AbilityManager itself switches the active ability for each slot given certain game criteria.\n2. The Ability has two or more forms which are encoded inside the script and switches between its forms given certain game criteria.\n\nI think the best way is no.1 because technically \"Interact\" will be an ability and it would be bad practice to encode an \"Interact\" ability inside every other ability just in case the player gains that ability.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-14012,
			"y":-3821,
			"width":541,
			"height":280
		},
		{
			"id":"383a3da57dc76cf5",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Aura\nAura is a reflection of the vitality of the arena. \n\nAura rises when the ecosystem is thriving (creatures/anthurium alive, ichor plentiful, terrain intact).\nAura falls when things are dying or being destroyed recklessly.\nThe player can drain Aura for short-term gain (kill things for special items/shards) or cultivate it for a stronger result screen score and a harder but richer Final Bloom. Aura at the moment the Final Bloom fires becomes the run's score multiplier.\n\nAura rises when\n- Creatures are alive and active (multiplied by how many different creature species are active on the map)\n- The anthurium spreads\n- Terrain is intact\n- Ichor is abundant\n\nAura falls when\n- Creatures die\n- The anthurium is suppressed or killed back\n- Terrain is destroyed\n- Ichor goes scarce\n\nScoring formula for round end:\n```\nFinal score\n =\t(Distinct creature species ever active x 200)\n +\t(Anamnesis at Final Bloom x 50)\n +\tif the player survives: (Aura at Final Bloom x 100)\n +\telse if the player dies: (Total Aura x 50)\n +\t(Boss completion bonus)\n -\t(Anthurium damage taken x 10)\n```\n\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-9905,
			"y":-3276,
			"width":520,
			"height":760
		},
		{
			"id":"bc60eb517af8ddbf",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"ui design\n\nfor menu\n\n```\ncontroller\n\tsub node\n\tsub node\n\tsub node\n```\n\nwhat can these nodes do?\n\nopen a new menu within same context\nlose/gain focus\nnavigate",
