			"height":100
		},
		{"id":"95a599150c996a59","type":"text","text":"we can still use these from way earlier!!!\ncreature personality traits\n\n**aggression**: affects hunting, attacking, territorial behavior\n**bravery**: affects fleeing, risk-taking, exploration\n**dominance**: affects leadership, pausing, submission\n**energy**: affects movement speed, activity level, rest\n**nervous**: affects fleeing, hiding, wariness\n**sympathy**: affects helping others, sharing, cooperation","x":-19410,"y":-2536,"width":560,"height":260},
		{
			"id":"5f3ee51e506cb1f1",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"how would i design entity reflection?\n\nreflection would only apply to \"projectiles\", not attacks based in melee, like a slash or bite.\n\nso a damaging entity will have a hurtbox; this hurtbox needs to have identification:\n- PROJECTILE\n- MELEE\n- FORCE\n- SELF\n- etc? not sure what else can be here\n\nthe hitbox can have properties that tell it what types of damage to respond to.",
