		},
		{
			"id":"2dd061a99712214f",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# Run-to-run progression\n\nThe player unlocks things based on\n- high scores\n- amount of runs played\n- unique quests completed?\n- achievements\n\nUnlockables include\n- Additional creature types that can appear in the dungeon\n- Additional bloom events\n- Additional terrain types (zones/biomes?)\n- Cosmetics for pip and other creatures\n- Bestiary pages\n- Additional fun modes\n- other things?",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11585,
			"y":-2656,
			"width":520,
			"height":480
		},
		{
			"id":"1578bc4a7aec6666",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"Setting cells from a library of the cells! :DDD\n\nCellData: holds data that is individual to each cell in the world\nCellType: describes one single cell type, including graphics and properties\n\n```gdscript\nextends Resource\nclass_name CellData\n\nvar type: CellType\nvar invisible = false\nvar max_health: float = 0\nvar health: float = 0\n```\n\n```gdscript\nextends Resource\nclass_name CellType\n\nenum TerrainType{GROUND, WALL, GAP, OUT_OF_BOUNDS}\n\n@export var terrain: TerrainType\n# tileset that this celltype points to\n@export var tileset_id: int\n# does this tileset tile or does it pick random textures from the tileset?\n@export var random_tile: bool\n# does this tileset tile with cells that don't own the same tileset_id?\n@export var tile_with_aliens: bool\n\n```\n\nEvery CellType resource file is stored in a `Dictionary[StringName, Resource]` inside a new script called `CellTypeRegistry`.\n\n```gdscript\nextends Node\n# autoload\n\nconst SCAN_PATHS: Array[String] = [\n\t\"res://resources/cell_types/\",\n\t\"user://mods/cell_types/\"\n]\n\nvar registry: Dictionary[StringName, String] = {}\n# StringName -> Resource (populated on first use)\nvar _cache: Dictionary[StringName, Resource] = {}\n\n```\n\nso essentially, it's a big lookup table that captures the basename of the resource file, and sets that as a key to the actual resource file.\n\nthen, the user can simply just call `WorldGrid.set_cell_by_type(type_name: StringName, world_pos: Vector2)` to set a cell to that type.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11780,
			"y":-1940,
			"width":620,
			"height":1180
		},
		{
			"id":"3c63b1fb557e2059",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"`WorldGrid.set_cell_by_type(type_name: StringName, world_pos: Vector2)`\n1. retrieve `CellData` from those coordinates\n2. retrieve `CellType` resource that maps to `type_name`\n3. set `CellData.type` = retrieved type\n4. call `WorldGrid.set_cell()`\n5. ",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11140,
			"y":-1820,
			"width":540,
			"height":350
		},
		{
			"id":"207229774af92456",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### BUMBLE\nMousy, goblinlike creatures with yellow skin. Primitive in mind\n\n---\n\n| Q                 | A                                                                |\n| ----------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Behavior class?   | PREDATORY CONSUMER                                               |\n| Reproduction?     | When ichor reserves are full, will reproduce with other Bumbles. |\n| Abilities?        | Throw a slow-moving spear.                                       |\n| Ecosystem role?   |                                                                  |\n| Behavior pattern? | Likes to be around other Bumbles.                                |\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12180,
			"y":635,
			"width":660,
			"height":500
		},
		{
			"id":"a666859beac034ef",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"# ENERGY CUBE GAMMA\n\n| Q                 | A                                                                                     |\n| ----------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Behavior class?   | ALOOF EXEMPT                                                                          |\n| Reproduction?     | does not reproduce. these are spawned from random events or interdimensional portals. |\n| Abilities?        | Detonate, causing a large explosion and dealing massive damage to nearby entities.    |\n| Ecosystem role?   |                                                                                       |\n| Behavior pattern? | Moves quickly and wanders around aimlessly. Detonates when it dies.                   |\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-11020,
			"y":635,
			"width":540,
			"height":420
		},
		{
			"id":"6098b1f5848c11f4",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"```csharp\nusing Godot;\nusing System.Collections.Generic;\n\npublic partial class Entity : CharacterBody2D\n{\n    // GDScript components keyed by their Script object (same as before)\n    private readonly Godot.Collections.Dictionary<Script, Godot.Collections.Array> _gdComponents = new();\n    // C# components keyed by System.Type — no GDScript object involved\n    private readonly Dictionary<System.Type, List<Component>> _csComponents = new();\n\n    [Signal] public delegate void EntityInitializedEventHandler();\n\n    public StringName basename { get; private set; }\n\n    public override void _Ready()\n    {\n        basename = GetBasename();\n        RegisterComponentsRecursive(this);\n        EmitSignal(SignalName.EntityInitialized);\n        MotionMode = MotionModeEnum.Floating;\n    }\n\n    private void RegisterComponentsRecursive(Node node)\n    {\n        foreach (var child in node.GetChildren())\n        {\n            if (child is Component c)\n                _RegisterComponent(c);\n            RegisterComponentsRecursive(child);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public void _RegisterComponent(Component component)\n    {\n        var script = component.GetScript().As<Script>();\n\n        if (script != null)\n        {\n            // GDScript component: walk script inheritance chain\n            var s = script;\n            while (s != null)\n            {\n                if (!_gdComponents.ContainsKey(s))\n                    _gdComponents[s] = new Godot.Collections.Array();\n                _gdComponents[s].Add(component);\n                s = s.GetBaseScript();\n            }\n            component.entity = this;\n            component.Call(\"_on_registered\"); // dispatches to GDScript override\n        }\n        else\n        {\n            // C# component: walk type inheritance chain\n            var t = component.GetType();\n            while (t != null && typeof(Component).IsAssignableFrom(t))\n            {\n                if (!_csComponents.ContainsKey(t))\n                    _csComponents[t] = new List<Component>();\n                _csComponents[t].Add(component);\n                t = t.BaseType;\n            }\n            component.entity = this;\n            component._on_registered(); // direct C# virtual dispatch\n        }\n\n        component.EmitSignal(Component.SignalName.Registered);\n    }\n\n    // GDScript: entity.add_component(to, component)\n    public void add_component(Node to, Component component)\n    {\n        _RegisterComponent(component);\n        to.AddChild(component);\n    }\n\n    // GDScript: entity.get_component(SomeGDScriptClass)\n    public Component get_component(Script type)\n    {\n        if (_gdComponents.TryGetValue(type, out var arr) && arr.Count > 0)\n            return (Component)arr[0];\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    // C#: entity.GetComponent<PhysicsComponent>() — no marshaling, no Script object\n    public T GetComponent<T>() where T : Component\n    {\n        if (_csComponents.TryGetValue(typeof(T), out var list) && list.Count > 0)\n            return (T)list[0];\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    public Godot.Collections.Array get_components(Script type)\n        => _gdComponents.TryGetValue(type, out var arr) ? arr : null;\n\n    public bool has_component(Script type)\n        => _gdComponents.TryGetValue(type, out var arr) && arr.Count > 0;\n\n    public bool HasComponent<T>() where T : Component\n        => _csComponents.TryGetValue(typeof(T), out var list) && list.Count > 0;\n\n    public StringName GetBasename()\n        => new StringName(SceneFilePath.GetFile().GetBaseName());\n\n    public static Entity FindEntity(Node node)\n    {\n        if (node == null) return null;\n        if (node is Entity e) return e;\n        return FindEntity(node.GetParent());\n    }\n}\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-19320,
			"y":900,
			"width":440,
			"height":1420
		},
		{
			"id":"ae27136b1155af95",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"```csharp\nusing Godot;\n\npublic partial class PhysicsComponent : Component\n{\n    // snake_case to match serialized scene data and existing GDScript callers\n    [Export] public bool disabled = false;\n    [Export] public float mass = 1.0f;\n    [Export] public float friction_coefficient = 1.0f;\n    [Export] public float base_friction = 800f;\n    [Export] public float restitution = 0.4f;\n    [Export] public float min_bounce_speed = 40.0f;\n    [Export] public float max_speed = 1000.0f;\n    [Export] public Node world_interface;  // WorldInterface in GDScript\n    [Export] public Node locomotion;       // LocomotionHandler in GDScript\n\n    private const float OverlapSeparationSpeed = 1500.0f;\n    private const float OverlapDepthThreshold = 1.0f;\n\n    public Vector2 physics_velocity = Vector2.Zero;\n    private Vector2 _accumulatedForce = Vector2.Zero;\n\n    [Signal] public delegate void WallCollisionEventHandler(Node source);       // \"wall_collision\"\n    [Signal] public delegate void EntityCollisionEventHandler(Entity source);   // \"entity_collision\"\n\n    public override void _PhysicsProcess(double delta)\n    {\n        if (disabled) return;\n        PhysicsUpdate((float)delta);\n    }\n\n    public void PhysicsUpdate(float delta)\n    {\n        ApplyForces(delta);\n        ApplyFriction(delta);\n\n        // cross-language property access — one marshaling call per frame, acceptable\n        var locoVel = locomotion != null\n            ? locomotion.Get(\"velocity\").As<Vector2>()\n            : Vector2.Zero;\n\n        var preSlideVelocity = physics_velocity;\n        var preSlideFull = physics_velocity + locoVel;\n\n        entity.Velocity = preSlideFull;\n        entity.MoveAndSlide();\n        physics_velocity = entity.Velocity - locoVel;\n\n        HandleCollisions(preSlideVelocity, preSlideFull);\n    }\n\n    public void clear_velocity() => physics_velocity = Vector2.Zero;\n\n    public void apply_impulse(Vector2 direction, float magnitude)\n        => physics_velocity += direction.Normalized() * (magnitude / mass);\n\n    public void apply_force(Vector2 direction, float magnitude)\n        => _accumulatedForce += direction.Normalized() * magnitude;\n\n    private void ApplyForces(float delta)\n    {\n        physics_velocity += (_accumulatedForce / mass) * delta;\n        _accumulatedForce = Vector2.Zero;\n        physics_velocity = physics_velocity.LimitLength(max_speed);\n    }\n\n    private void ApplyFriction(float delta)\n    {\n        float decel = base_friction * friction_coefficient / mass;\n        physics_velocity = physics_velocity.MoveToward(Vector2.Zero, decel * delta);\n    }\n\n    private void HandleCollisions(Vector2 preVelocity, Vector2 preFull)\n    {\n        int count = entity.GetSlideCollisionCount();\n        for (int i = 0; i < count; i++)\n        {\n            var col = entity.GetSlideCollision(i);\n            var normal = col.GetNormal();\n            var collider = col.GetCollider();\n\n            if (collider is StaticBody2D || collider is TileMapLayer)\n            {\n                var relVel = col.GetColliderVelocity() - physics_velocity;\n                float push = relVel.Dot(normal);\n                if (push > 0f)\n                    physics_velocity += normal * push;\n\n                if (preVelocity.Length() > min_bounce_speed && preVelocity.Dot(normal) < 0f)\n                {\n                    physics_velocity = preVelocity.Bounce(normal) * restitution;\n                    EmitSignal(SignalName.WallCollision, (Node)col.GetCollider());\n                }\n            }\n            else if (collider is Entity otherEntity)\n            {\n                // fully native — both types are C#, zero marshaling\n                var otherPhysics = otherEntity.GetComponent<PhysicsComponent>();\n                float intoNormal = preFull.Dot(normal);\n\n                if (otherPhysics != null)\n                {\n                    if (intoNormal < 0f)\n                    {\n                        float m1 = mass, m2 = otherPhysics.mass;\n                        bool dominant = m1 > m2 || (m1 == m2 && entity.GetInstanceId() < otherEntity.GetInstanceId());\n\n                        if (dominant)\n                        {\n                            float total = m1 + m2;\n                            var axis = -normal;\n                            float vA = -intoNormal;\n                            float vB = otherPhysics.physics_velocity.Dot(axis);\n                            float e = (restitution + otherPhysics.restitution) * 0.5f;\n\n                            float newVa = (m1 * vA + m2 * vB + m2 * e * (vB - vA)) / total;\n                            float newVb = (m1 * vA + m2 * vB + m1 * e * (vA - vB)) / total;\n\n                            physics_velocity += axis * (newVa - vA);\n                            otherPhysics.physics_velocity += axis * (newVb - vB);\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n                else\n                {\n                    if (intoNormal < 0f)\n                        physics_velocity -= normal * intoNormal;\n                }\n\n                if (col.GetDepth() > OverlapDepthThreshold)\n                    entity.GlobalPosition += Vector2.FromAngle((float)GD.Randf() * Mathf.Tau);\n\n                EmitSignal(SignalName.EntityCollision, otherEntity);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n```",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-18800,
			"y":1000,
			"width":620,
			"height":1400
		},
		{
			"id":"d7d59d25110a2342",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"```csharp\nusing Godot;\n\npublic partial class Component : Node\n{\n    public Entity entity;\n\n    [Signal]\n    public delegate void RegisteredEventHandler(); // exposed as \"registered\"\n\n    public virtual void _on_registered() { }\n}\n```",
