			"y":1735,
			"width":260,
			"height":60
		},
		{
			"id":"a2b879c3caea8c04",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### DRILLHOG\nMassive, porcine creature with drills for tusks. Moves with weight; slowly turns and charges powerfully.",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12170,
			"y":-265,
			"width":880,
			"height":200
		},
		{
			"id":"1df4cce560a11f2a",
			"type":"text",
			"text":"### GRUBBA\nFat pale segmented larva. It wiggles occasionally, clearly soft, harmless, and tasty.\n\n---\n\n| Q                 | A                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      |\n| ----------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Behavior class?   | PASSIVE CONSUMER                                                                                                                                                                                                                       |\n| Reproduction?     | When ichor reserves are high, splits into two half-sized Grubbas.                                                                                                                                                                      |\n| Abilities?        | 1. Curls into a ball and launches forward like a bowling ball, knocking back and dealing slight damage to entities. This ability can be charged for a faster launch.<br>2. Grows larger in size if its ichor reserves are high enough. |\n| Ecosystem role?   | Grubba is the main food source for predatory beasts. If grubs are thriving, then predatory creatures are bound to be less aggressive.                                                                                                  |\n| Behavior pattern? | Slowly wanders and wiggles around, tending to hang around food sources as it cannot move very fast unless escaping.                                                                                                                    |\n",
			"styleAttributes":{},
			"x":-12180,
			"y":1175,
			"width":700,
			"height":460
		},
		{"id":"22d24c7372b648d7","type":"text","text":"\n| Forget-me-not creatures                                                                                                    | Anthurium analog            |\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- |\n| Grunt <br>Steps around, attacks nearby creatuers                                                                           | crab guy<br>Bimpy           |\n| Grunto <br>Steps around, occasionally fire a projectile, attacks nearby creatures                                          | crab guy 2<br>Bagabimpy     |\n| Grunta <br>Steps around quickly, rapidly attacks nearby creatures                                                          | crab guy 3<br>Bimporg       |\n| Energycube <br>Constantly moves around erratically, lots of health                                                         | ecube beta                  |\n| Frog <br>Hops around, sometimes long distances                                                                             |                             |\n| Bomb<br>Steps around, sets a timer to detonation when attacked, attacks nearby creatures                                   |                             |\n| Gunner<br>Steps around, shoots projectiles rapidly when creature is in LOS                                                 | crab guy 4<br>Bormose Bimpy |\n| Dungeoncube Alpha<br>Rapidly slides around the map in cardinal directions, kills anything it slides into                   | dcube alpha                 |\n| Dungeoncube Beta<br>Slides around the map in cardinal directions, kills anything it slides into                            | dcube beta                  |\n| Slimer<br>Steps around slowly, attacks nearby creatures, leaves a solid slime trail, dies when unable to make another move |                             |\n| Ghost<br>Steps around, shoots bombs behind it when it steps                                                                |                             |\n| Cloner<br>Grunt AI, duplicates itself when shot by a projectile                                                            |                             |\n| Unstablecube<br>Energycube AI, explodes when killed                                                                        | ecube gamma                 |\n| Bandit<br>Moves constantly quickly, seeks treasure and runs around with it                                                 |                             |\n| Worm<br>Moves constantly, attacks creatures in front of it                                                                 |                             |\n| Pinwheel<br>Moves constantly, is more likely to turn in one direction                                                      |                             |\n| Spider<br>Hops around when nearby other creatures                                                                          |                             |\nseems like the base creature takes a step where it's facing, then decides if it wants to face a different direction.","x":-16120,"y":30,"width":1180,"height":900},
		{"id":"682deebbfbe4d1ff","type":"file","file":"Pasted image 20260620124534.png","x":-15640,"y":1015,"width":400,"height":312}
